## Problem description

There are two types of goods (goods1, goods2), one truck (truck1), one market (market1), one depot (depot1), and two possible levels (level0, level1). The truck truck1 has no goods of type goods1 and no goods2 loaded. The depot has no goods of type goods1 and no goods2 stored. The market market1 has one level of goods of type goods1 and one level of goods2 for sale. No goods of type goods1 and none of goods2 have been purchased yet at market1. The truck is currently at depot1. The goal is to store 1 level of goods of type goods1 and 1 level of goods2 at the depot.
